rComments: He is a fantastic professor! Really makes sure you have an understanding of physiology, and he is funny too. Grade professor!

Great prof. He really seems to genuinely care about how you do in the class. His midterms were extremely fair, and if you pay attention in class and study the diagrams, you're pretty well set. I'd recommend his class for sure.

He made learning the entire skeleton and every single muscle beyond bearable. The exams were very fair. I'm not going to lie, he's gorgeous, which helped, but the real remarkable thing about him and his teaching is how hard he tries to make the material memorable, and palatable.   Would def take again.

Kyle was a great prof! He replies to emails quickly and is clear and helpful. His lectures are easy to pay attention to: powerpoint, projector, questionanswer, and brought in bones for us to look at to understand more easily. He cares about his students a lot. Only criticism was some material was rushed at the end. Midterms are tough but fair.
AMAZING PROFESSOR. GAV GREAT LECTURES AND WAS TOTALLY ENCOURAGING AND WELCOMING. WOULD TAKE HIS CLASS AGAIN IN A HEART BEAT. plus he's gorgeous so that's good.
Loved his lectures, uses different teaching methods, asks alot of questions in class, so reading the textbook before lecture should help you understand what he's asking

Awesome and interesting lectures and a very well organized course. He told the class right away what they needed to do in order to do well and sent out the readings a week early. Super helpful and approachable.
